---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const effectiveDate = 'July 13, 2026';
const basePath = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
---

<Base title="Terms of Service" description="SPRITEbot terms of service.">
  <section class="page-hero legal-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Terms of Service</p>
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p>Effective {effectiveDate}</p>
  </section>

  <div class="legal-content">
    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Agreement</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of SPRITEbot ("the Bot"), a Discord
        application operated by the SPRITEbot team ("we," "us," "our"). By using the Bot, you
        agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Bot.
      </p>
      <p>
        These Terms are between you and us. They do not replace, modify, or
        override <a href="https://discord.com/terms">Discord's Terms of Service</a> or <a href="https://discord.com/guidelines">Community Guidelines</a>,
        which also apply to your use of the Bot.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Eligibility</h2>
      <p>
        You must meet Discord's minimum age requirement (13 years or the minimum age in your
        country, whichever is higher) to use the Bot. By using SPRITEbot, you confirm that you
        meet this requirement.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You may not use the Bot to submit, distribute, or interact with content that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Violates Discord's Terms of Service or Community Guidelines</li>
        <li>Constitutes harassment, abuse, or threats toward others</li>
        <li>Promotes hate speech, discrimination, or extremist content</li>
        <li>Contains sexually explicit or violent material</li>
        <li>Attempts to exploit, dox, or harm others in any way</li>
        <li>Interferes with the Bot's operation or attempts to abuse its systems</li>
        <li>Violates any applicable local, national, or international laws</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Subscriptions and Billing</h2>
      <p>
        SPRITEbot offers a paid Premium tier that unlocks additional features for an entire
        Discord server. Subscriptions are purchased and managed through Discord's built-in
        subscription system.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          All billing, payment processing, and refunds are handled by Discord. We do not directly
          collect payment information.
        </li>
        <li>
          Subscription terms, renewal, and cancellation follow
          <a href="https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/4407269525911">Discord's subscription policies</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          Cancelling a subscription ends Premium access at the close of the current billing
          period. No partial refunds are issued for unused time.
        </li>
        <li>
          We reserve the right to change pricing with reasonable notice. Price changes take effect
          at the start of your next billing period.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Service Availability</h2>
      <p>
        SPRITEbot is provided on a best-effort basis. We do not guarantee any specific uptime,
        availability, or response time. The Bot may be temporarily unavailable for maintenance,
        updates, or reasons beyond our control.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the event of extended outages affecting paid subscribers, we may offer service credits
        or billing adjustments at our discretion, but we are not obligated to do so.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Enforcement</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to suspend or permanently revoke access for users who violate these
        Terms. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Blocking the user or associated account from accessing the Bot</li>
        <li>Reporting misconduct to Discord Trust &amp; Safety</li>
        <li>Revoking access without notice or refund where warranted</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        You retain ownership of content you create through the Bot (characters, game
        configurations, roleplay text). By using the Bot, you grant us a limited license to
        store and process that content as needed for the Bot to function.
      </p>
      <p>
        SPRITEbot's name, branding, and code remain our property.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        The Bot is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, express
        or implied. We disclaim all warranties including merchantability, fitness for a
        particular purpose, and non-infringement.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are not responsible for user-submitted content, data loss resulting from service
        interruptions, or the consequences of interactions initiated through the Bot.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, we are not liable for any indirect, incidental,
        special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the Bot. Our total
        liability for any claim related to the Bot is limited to the amount you paid us (if any)
        in the twelve months preceding the claim.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms at any time. Material changes will be communicated through the
        Bot's support channels or website. Continued use of the Bot after changes are posted
        constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about these Terms, contact the SPRITEbot maintainer through
        the <a href="https://discord.gg/eXktxzKxze">support server</a> or the
        contact channels linked from the Bot.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
